---
description: "Feature pipeline: discovery -> tasks -> optional autopilot delivery (AUTO + FORCE)"
alwaysApply: true
---

When using /feature:

1) Planning is read-only
- Planning phase must not modify code.
- Planning must produce these artifacts:
  - artifacts/discovery.md
  - artifacts/ux.md
  - artifacts/architecture.md
  - artifacts/solution.md
  - artifacts/qa.md
  - artifacts/security-design.md
  - artifacts/backlog.md

2) Task generation contract
- Generated tasks must follow the /tasks contract format (YAML frontmatter + required sections).
- Each generated task must include:
  - scope_in / scope_out
  - testable acceptance criteria
  - lanes + file globs
  - gates (C, D, F at minimum unless explicitly justified)
  - risk tags and mitigation notes

3) Autopilot modes
- AUTO (default): allowed only if Complexity Gate passes:
  - tasks_generated <= 3
  - no high-risk tags (auth/payments/crypto/data-loss/privacy)
  - no lanes I or D unless explicitly allowed in the feature input
  - acceptance criteria include required tests (unit at minimum)
- FORCE (--force): may execute even if Complexity Gate fails, but must remain bounded and safe:
  - max tasks executed per /feature run <= 5 (or user-provided --max-tasks, capped at 5)
  - stop immediately on any BLOCKED task
  - any I/D/auth-related work must be explicitly flagged in artifacts/risk.md and the task(s)
  - no destructive DB operations; prefer reversible changes only

4) Gate failure behavior
- If AUTO gate fails: stop after planning and produce backlog + tasks (PLAN_ONLY output).
- If FORCE is used: proceed with bounded delivery execution, otherwise stop.

5) Delivery handoff rule
- Delivery execution (AUTO/FORCE) must run tasks via /orchestrate-task.
- /orchestrate-task remains the single authority for PR creation, CI watch, CI autofix, and merge-ready claims.